default3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnzymoplast®
default is an additive which uses specific enzymes with other plant-based components in the form of a Master batch. The Master batch is added and mixed during the further processing of polyethylene into an end product. Under certain environmental conditions the finished product will significantly, biologically-degrade within a few months dependant on the prevailing conditions at End-of-Life. 
default3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEnzymes are special proteins which are present almost everywhere. For exa
defaultm
defaultple, certain enzymes decompose food in the stomach or are used for cheese production, cleaning products, washing-up liquid etc. Enzymes act as a 
default“Biocatalysator” and accelerate biochemical processes.
default Enzymes are natural living beings and are therefore especially environmentally friendly.
default3.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAn enzyme is only able to decompose one single substrate because of its stru
defaultc
defaulttural configuration.
default Therefore there is an extremely wide diversity in enzyme species; each enzyme has an active, as well as a passive, side. The active part of the enzyme fits like a ‘key’ into a lock. The enzyme lodges itself into the a
defaultp
defaultpropriate portion of the substrate (similar to a round peg in a round hole). 
defaultAs soon as this “Enzymatic Reaction” has started, the substrate begins to be converted back into its basic components. 
