default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA further challenge is how to keep the enzyme alive at high temperatures. E
defaultn
defaultzymes normally start to die from a temperature of about 100°C. 
defaultTherefore the enzymes are especially encapsulated during the production pro
defaultc
defaultess to withstand temperatures in extrusion of up to 300°
defaultC
default. The precise process of 
defaultencapsulation 
defaultforms part of the IP.
default3.10
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe enzymes used do not have a negative influence on the mechanical chara
defaultc
defaultteristics of the end products. According to third party tests the characteristics show improvement by as much as 2-3%. However, these values cannot be standardised due to the variety of and types of polyolefin and therefore serves only as a rough guideline.
defaultFact 1. Because Enzymoplast is mixed with pure Polyethylene it is possible to recycle ENZO-PE films with other polyethylene products without contaminating the esta
defaultb
defaultlished standard polymer recycling stream. Due to the possibility of improvement of the mechanical strength the number of recycling processes may increase. Furthe
defaultr
defaultmore, Enzymoplast does not use any stabilizers to handle the timeframe of biodegr
defaulta
defaultdation. Hence, there is no negative effect as stabilisers weaken polyethylene after a determined time.
